<plot>'New Sincerity' is a comedy that gently, but firmly addresses a tendency in culture to sugarcoat everything: The comfortingly patriarchal President of the United States announces that, due to global warming, the world will end in a matter of minutes. Laughing gas is consequently released to quiet the populace. Suddenly the inconvenient truth of our own demise is rendered surprisingly convenient.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?394232</url></doc>
